%N A396599 Odd numbers k where sigma_2(k)/k is an integer.
%H A396599 Alexander Violette, <a href="/A396599/b396599.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..104</a>
%H A396599 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Divisor_function">Divisor function</a>.
%e A396599 65's divisors are 1, 5, 13, and 65. Since (1^2+5^2+13^2+65^2)/65 is an integer, 65 is in this sequence.
%t A396599 Select[Range[1, 4000000, 2], Divisible[DivisorSigma[2, #], #] &] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 03 2026 *)
%o A396599 (PARI) isok(k) = (k%2) && (denominator(sigma(k, 2)/k) == 1); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jun 03 2026
